results.name: Least nonnegative m such that n!-m is prime.
comment: Conjecture: for n >= 3, a(n) is 1 or a prime. - _Amarnath Murthy_, Mar 19 2002
a(n) is not divisible by any prime <= n. If a(n) > 1 is composite, then a(n) > n^2. There are no entries up to n = 2000 with a(n) > n^2, and there may be none. - _Robert Israel_, Jul 20 2014
link: T. D. Noe and Hans Havermann (T. D. Noe to 500), Table of n, a(n) for n = 2..2000
